The paper discusses a process for deriving a delta language from the grammar of a given base language, which falls under the category of software engineering (cs.SE). The paper also mentions the use of statecharts, which are a type of programming language, indicating a connection to programming languages (cs.PL). The paper involves the use of machine learning techniques for language extension, which falls under the category of machine learning (cs.LG). The paper also discusses the application of delta modeling in the context of temporal and spatial variability, which is relevant to artificial intelligence (cs.AI) and control systems (cs.SY).
